Encore Capital Group, Inc., and subsidiaries form the largest publicly traded debt buyer by revenue in the United States.[2][3]:235[4] They purchase "portfolios of defaulted consumer receivables from major banks, credit unions, and utility providers,"[5] and recover collectable debt from these accounts. Jake Halpern author of Bad Paper, described Encore Capital as a "behemoth" in the American debt-industry complex.[6] At the corporate level debt collection is highly profitable and Encore Capital enjoyed soaring revenues from $316 million in 2009 to $773 million in 2013.[6] The firm is a publicly traded NASDAQ Global Select company, a component stock of the Russell 2000, the S&P SmallCap 600, and the Wilshire 4500.
