ge in short interest from the previous report to the most recent report. Exchanges report short interest twice a month. Percent of Float Total short positions relative to the number of shares available to trade.      Short Interest (06/30/17)    Shares Sold Short 4.67 M     Change from Last  -1.45%      Percent of Float 18.56%       ?    Money Flow Uptick/Downtick Ratio Money flow measures the relative buying and selling pressure on a stock, based on the value of trades made on an "uptick" in price and the value of trades made on a "downtick" in price. The up/down ratio is calculated by dividing the value of uptick trades by the value of downtick trades. Net money flow is the value of uptick trades minus the value of downtick trades. Our calculations are based on comprehensive, delayed quotes.      Stock Money Flow    Uptick/Downtick Trade Ratio  0 2    0.63      Net Money Flow ($)  -62,660    Money flow gives a snapshot of relative buying and selling pressure in a stock. A ratio above one suggests greater buying pressure, below one suggests greater selling.               Advertisement         Competitors ECPG      Company Change P/E (TTM)    ASFI Asta Funding Inc.   -0.70% -0.05   -     NICK Nicholas Financial Inc.   -1.47% -0.13   12.78     CACC Credit Acceptance Corp.   +0.48% +1.21   14.42     LOAN Manhattan Bridge Capital Inc.   -0.76% -0.04   14.34     AXP American Express Co.   -1.24% -1.06   17.22     ATLC Atlanticus Holdings Corp.   - -   -     PRAA PRA Group Inc.   -1.79% -0.70   17.66        More information on ECPG   Competitor Data Provided By: capital cube           Profile ECPG      Encore Capital Group, Inc. provides debt management and recovery solutions for consumers and property owners across a broad range of financial assets. It operates through the Portfolio Purchasing and Recovery segment. The Portfolio Purchasing and Recovery segment purchases...      3111 Camino del Rio North San Diego California 92108 United States   Email Website Map       